This paper is focused on the optimization methods used in training neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses numerical analysis techniques to analyze the convergence of the momentum method, which suggests the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of momentum methods in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. Finally, the paper discusses the dynamic behavior of the momentum method, which could be relevant to the category of control systems (cs.SY).
